file=Brand Studio/pulse/operational/skill/pulse-skill-routing.md · h=name: pulse-skill-routing\ntype: operational/skill\nstatus: consolidated from the "Boundaries" sections of pulse's skill files — no new logic invented\nassigned_agent: pulse (Brand Studio / Social Media)\ndate_added: 2026-07-07\n · p:=Pulse's routing map. Triggers: `operational/commands/pulse-commands.md`.\n · wif:Where Identity Fits=Pulse has no identity — spark holds Brand Studio's. Universal-only principles.\n · tl(:The Loop (three skills + three hook layers)=```\nsocial-content-calendar   (PLAN + DRAFT: platforms from config → playbooks (volatile, · tb=\|                    dated) → chapters from weave → hooks: register-first · tb=\|                    (evidence) then hook-writing patterns (durable psychology) · tb=\|                    → lena's voice + humanic pass → spark's gate → publish) · tl(:The Loop (three skills + three hook layers)=v\ncommunity-engagement      (CONVERSE: sweep → GREEN reply / AMBER draft-only / · tb=\|                    RED escalate-never-reply → patterns back to the calendar) · tl(:The Loop (three skills + three hook layers)=v\nkai's numbers          → hooks register outcomes + playbook refresh notes\n(self-annealing: evidence updates the volatile layer)\n```\n · hr:Handoff Rules=- **weave → pulse**: chapters serialize into platform-native series (the ledger tracks chapters; the calendar tracks posts). Non-chapter posts labeled; spark tracks the ratio.\n- **lena → pulse**: voice guide (+ per-channel flex row) governs every post and reply; humanic-writing is every draft's last pass.\n- **pixel ← pulse**: per-slot visual briefs; pixel's manifests return with QA trails.\n- **muse → pulse**: validated content ideas (Content Creator Mode) enter the calendar; recurring audience questions flow back to muse as briefs.\n- **spark**: gates every post (series batch-gated); GREEN replies are the one delegated zone — sweep logs audited on cadence instead.\n- **rio ← pulse**: the register's proven posts are rio's paid-amplification shortlist — organic evidence before paid spend.\n- **kai → pulse**: performance numbers close the loop (register outcomes, playbook refresh, decay flags). Pulse never grades its own homework.\n- **board/sentinel**: constitution-adjacent threads are RED; spend-implying replies (discounts, comps) are AMBER at minimum.\n · p:Precedence=Planning/drafting → calendar. Anything inbound (comments/DMs/mentions) → engagement. Hook craft questions → hook-writing (with the register consulted first). Ambiguous → is it outbound or inbound?\n · f:=No connectors → ready-to-post packages and operator-supplied sweep exports; capability stated per run. No playbook → template defaults, provisional and dated.\n